.START 

National Datacomputer Inc., a maker of hand-held computers and data collection devices, said it received two orders totaling $2 million. 

Under one contract, the Billerica, Mass.-based company will sell $1.5 million of its 3.0 Datacomputer over a 21-month period. 

In the second $500,000 contract, the company will sell hand-held computer route accounting systems.
The company, which didn't disclose who awarded the contracts, said revenue for the second shipment will be reported in the fourth quarter. 

In 1988, the company had a loss of $1.7 million on revenue of $3.5 million. 

